name: Walter Phillips Gallery
directions: The Walter Phillips Gallery is located within Glyde Hall, which is across the street from the Sally Borden recreation building. The Gallery is on the first level. The accessibility ramp is located via the loading dock driveway to the left of the building. Glyde Hall is open 7 days a week, generally from 7:30am to 10:30ish pm. The Gender-Neutral and accessible, locking single-use restroom with a changing table is also located on the ground level. To find it, walk straight through the lobby of the Gallery and towards the grey stairs that lead up into Glyde Hall. At the foot of the stairs, turn left and you will see the door of the restroom. This is the only gender neutral restroom inside Glyde Hall, but there are a few others located in other Banff Centre buildings.
comment: This restroom is free for the public to use. The Gallery is also free to visit :).
